Context:
Mathematics course:
- Prepares students for degree level studies in various disciplines
- Taught at St. James "A" building, 200 King Street East
- Duration: 15 weeks (daytime courses only: 1 pm to 4 pm Tuesday to Thursday)
- Mid-point and end of course, students create and present a problem using skills and concepts learned
- For more information about U-Level Bridging program: email gbcdegreebridging@georgebrown.ca or call (416) 415-5000 ext. 3683

Statistics:
- Students learn data management, organization and analysis using statistical methods
- Role of data in statistical studies will be investigated
- Students will solve probability problems involving single or multiple events
- Students will analyze and draw conclusions from one and two-variable data using numerical, graphical and algebraic summaries

Location:
- Degree Preparation courses held at St. James "A" building, 200 King Street East

Contact Information:
